Buffalo City Municipality traffic officers found 37 school children crammed into a Toyota Quantum minibus taxi when the pulled over the vehicle in East London on Thursday.The Daily Dispatch reported that the Toyota Quantum was stopped along the Mdantsane Access Road.Not only was it certified to carry 15 passengers the vehicle was inspected and found to be unroadworthy. The driver who was promptly arrested was not in possession of a driver s licence or a Professional Driving Permit. 